comment.narrative:
Institutional, regulatory and technical and inter-ministerial coordination capacities strengthened. 
Internal and External Water Committee’s capacity to demonstrate global best practices and negotiation skills in water management and negotiation skills on trans boundary water issues enhanced;
Numbers of Water Security Initiatives developed and international network established ;

For Activity 1 (JCMC-JCC Coordination), one out of two milestones has been achieved and the second is progressing through gradual improvement of capacity and establishment of structured coordination systems and mechanisms. 
For Activity  2 (JCMC Capacity Building), two out of six milestones have been achieved, two are progressing as planned through gradual building up of capacity, systems and procedures and the achievement of two have been delayed but measures are put in place to ensure delivery in Q3 and Q4. The main challenge related to output 2 is the lack of staff that severely limits the ability of the JCMC to absorb capacity-building measures and reach institutional development targets. Consequently, UNDP has mobilized resources and planned out all activities but is on standby for intervention when JCMC has enough staff;
For Activity 3 (JCC Support), 1 out of 6 milestones has been achieved, three are progressing as planned and two are delayed but measures are put in place to ensure delivery in Q3 and Q4
